HEADWORD: Coypu
<hw>Coy"pu</hw> <pr>(koi"p??)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South American rodent
(<spn>Myopotamus coypus</spn>), allied to the beaver. It produces a
valuable fur called <prod>nutria</prod>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>coypou</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coystrel</ent>⟦br⟧
